# KartaLink | HQueue Render
___

## Category
Kartaverse/KartaLink/Scripts

## Author
Andrew Hazelden

## Version

___

## Description
<img width='270' height='41' src='data:image/png;base64,'/>

<p>Are you currently using Houdini HQueue to manage the 3D rendering jobs on your render farm? If that is the case then you might find the following comp script handy:</p>

<p>The "HQueue Render.py" comp script allows Fusion Studio to submit compositing jobs for rendering via Houdini HQueue. The script works great in both a "local queue", and for larger render farm usage scenarios.</p>

<h2>Script Compatibility</h2>
<p>Right now the script has been tested successfully with HQueue Server on macOS and Linux.</p>

<p>Windows support is currently under development. On Windows the following error is reported by HQueue when a job is run:</p>
<blockquote>&#91;WinError 2&#93; The system cannot find the file specified<br>
ERROR: Could not run command.</blockquote>
